n01440764.name: tench
n01440764.description: freshwater dace-like game fish of Europe and western Asia noted for ability to survive outside water

n01443537.name: goldfish
n01443537.description: small golden or orange-red freshwater fishes of Eurasia used as pond or aquarium fishes

n01484850.name: great_white_shark
n01484850.description: large aggressive shark widespread in warm seas; known to attack humans

n01491361.name: tiger_shark
n01491361.description: large dangerous warm-water shark with striped or spotted body

n01494475.name: hammerhead
n01494475.description: medium-sized live-bearing shark with eyes at either end of a flattened hammer-shaped head; worldwide in warm waters; can be dangerous

n01496331.name: electric_ray
n01496331.description: any sluggish bottom-dwelling ray of the order Torpediniformes having a rounded body and electric organs on each side of the head capable of emitting strong electric discharges

n01498041.name: stingray
n01498041.description: large venomous ray with large barbed spines near the base of a thin whiplike tail capable of inflicting severe wounds
